        Description copied from interface: MoneroWallet
        Get incoming and outgoing transfers to and from this wallet. An outgoing transfer represents a total amount sent from one or more subaddresses within an account to individual destination addresses, each with their own amount. An incoming transfer represents a total amount received into a subaddress within an account. Transfers belong to transactions which are stored on the blockchain. Query results can be filtered by passing in a MoneroTransferQuery. Transfers must meet every criteria defined in the query in order to be returned. All filtering is optional and no filtering is applied when not defined.
